strategy: Use complete cases only for core variables (liberalism, restrictionism, generation)
pros: Most conservative, no bias from imputation
cons: Reduced sample size, potential selection bias

strategy: Multiple imputation for variables with <30% missing, complete cases for generation
pros: Good balance of sample size and data quality

strategy: Multiple imputation for all variables with <50% missing, careful sensitivity analysis
pros: Maximum sample size, most power for analysis
